// Afterlife = a triggered ability [CR#702.135a]: "Afterlife N" means "When this
// permanent is put into a graveyard from the battlefield, create N 1/1 white
// and black Spirit creature tokens with flying." The printed N is the macro's
// `Count` param (the parser emits the bare numeral `Afterlife(2)`, read as
// `Count::Literal(2)` for `Param(0)`); multiple instances trigger separately
// ([CR#702.135b]).
//
// Pieces (all representable over existing primitives):
//   - trigger:        `ThisDies` — the `ZoneMove(what: Ref(This), from:
//                     Battlefield, to: Graveyard)` macro ([CR#700.4]).
//   - resolution:     `Create(Param(0), Token(…))` — create N token permanents
//                     ([CR#111.1]) of an INLINE creature token whose defined
//                     characteristics ([CR#111.3]) are: color White ∧ Black via
//                     a color indicator ([CR#202.2e] — a token has no mana cost,
//                     so its color rides the indicator), a Creature Spirit, 1/1
//                     (`power`/`toughness`), and the flying keyword ability
//                     (`Keyword(Flying)`, [CR#702.9]).
//
// The Spirit subtype is spelled INLINE as `Subtype(name: "Spirit", types:
// [Creature, Kindred])` — exactly what the bare `CreatureType(name: "Spirit")`
// macro ([CR#205.3m]) expands to — rather than the bare `Spirit` invocation,
// because the concrete creature-subtype macros are GENERATED under
// `plugins/wizards/` (gitignored) and so aren't in the `plugins/builtin`-only
// load the keyword-expansion test exercises. `Keyword(Flying)` is a builtin
// macro and is invoked normally.
//
// No engine gap: the inline `Token` already carries `color_indicator`, `types`,
// `subtypes`, `power`, `toughness`, and `abilities` — every field this 1/1 W/B
// Spirit-with-flying needs. Graduation (parse + round-trip) holds: this body
// expands to valid RON and round-trips.
(
    name: "Afterlife",
    template: "afterlife ${0}",
    kinds: [KeywordAbility],
    params: [Count],
    body: Composite(
        name: "Afterlife",
        abilities: [Triggered(
            event: ThisDies,
            effect: Create(Param(0), Token(
                color_indicator: [White, Black],
                types: [Creature],
                subtypes: [Subtype(name: "Spirit", types: [Creature, Kindred])],
                abilities: [Keyword(Flying)],
                power: 1,
                toughness: 1,
            )),
        )],
    ),
)
